On Debian 9 "stretch" and later, the dirmngr package needs to be installed before importing the key:
  sudo apt install dirmngr
Ubuntu 16.04 "Xenial", Debian 9 "stretch" and Debian Sid packages are signed with SHA2 key id 0xF1656F24C74CD1D8 since about 2016-07-04 (jira.mariadb.org/browse/MDEV-9781).


Version Mismatch Between MariaDB and Ubuntu/Debian Repositories
---------------------------------------------------------------
As mentioned here (and in MDEV-4080 and MDEV-3882) sometimes APT will refuse to install MariaDB.
Or, if MariaDB is already installed, suggest the removal of MariaDB to apply an upgrade to the mysql-common or libmysqlclient packages.

There are three primary ways of fixing this issue:

1 Specify specific version to install ('apt-get dist-upgrade' still breaks it)
2 Pin MariaDB repository
3 Hold packages

Pinning MariaDB Repository
==========================
Pin the MariaDB repository so its packages have higher priority then the ones from the system repositories.
Create a file with the '.pref' extension in '/etc/apt/preferences.d/' with the following contents:

Package: *
Pin: origin <mirror-domain>
Pin-Priority: 1000

Replace '<mirror-domain>' with the domain name of the MariaDB mirror you use. For example 'ftp.osuosl.org'

Holding Packages
================
To prevent 'apt-get dist-upgrade' from removing MariaDB compatible libmysqlclient and mysql-common
you can hold them: (as root)

echo libmysqlclient18 hold | dpkg --set-selections
echo mysql-common hold | dpkg --set-selections

When you want e.g. upgrade MariaDB and are ready to remove the holds:

echo libmysqlclient18 install | dpkg --set-selections
echo mysql-common install | dpkg --set-selections


Specifying Specific Versions to Install
=======================================
A way to fix this is to specify the exact version of the two packages that you want to install.
To do this, first determine the full version numbers of the affected packages:

apt-cache show mysql-common     | grep Version
apt-cache show libmysqlclient18 | grep Version
